      "note_no": "24",
      "note": "Since caring and striving for the good of the hereafter presupposes belief in God and in man's responsibility before Him, it is obvious that the term \"believer\" relates, in this context, to a cognition of God's absolute oneness and uniqueness as well as to a willing acceptance of the guidance offered to man through prophetic revelation. - In the original, the whole preceding sentence has the singular form (\"he who cares ... and strives ... and is a believer\"); but in view of the next clause, which is expressed in the plural, it is preferable to render these pronouns, agreeably with Arabic usage, uniformly in the plural."
